1
00:00:01,210 --> 00:00:03,710
(Episode 93)

2
00:00:17,320 --> 00:00:18,320
Yes.

3
00:00:23,400 --> 00:00:25,700
Nothing to report yet.

4
00:00:26,460 --> 00:00:28,870
Don't worry. I'm watching her like a hawk.

5
00:00:38,040 --> 00:00:39,210
Where am I?

6
00:00:39,980 --> 00:00:43,680
First, I need to figure out
what happened while I was bedridden.

7
00:00:44,220 --> 00:00:47,090
Pretending I've woken up can wait.

8
00:00:47,990 --> 00:00:50,590
Why on earth was I left here all alone?

9
00:00:51,990 --> 00:00:53,060
(Complaint)

10
00:00:53,120 --> 00:00:54,330
(Plaintiff: Han Young Ja,
Defendant: Chae Hwa Young)

11
00:00:54,390 --> 00:00:55,560
(Relief Sought)

12
00:00:55,630 --> 00:00:57,030
(Grounds for Claim)

13
00:00:57,260 --> 00:00:59,630
What is all this?

14
00:00:59,760 --> 00:01:03,070
Oh, my. It's a lawsuit
for emotional damages.

15
00:01:03,330 --> 00:01:06,600
Goodness. This was bound to happen.

16
00:01:07,270 --> 00:01:08,540
This is...

17
00:01:09,070 --> 00:01:11,340
A lawsuit for damages?

18
00:01:11,880 --> 00:01:13,110
What is the meaning of all this?

19
00:01:13,450 --> 00:01:16,650
That's just a misunderstanding
on her part, Father.

20
00:01:16,750 --> 00:01:18,750
It's no misunderstanding, Chairman.

21
00:01:20,390 --> 00:01:23,890
CEO Chae Hwa Young
is having an affair with my husband.

22
00:01:24,320 --> 00:01:25,460
Honey!

23
00:01:25,520 --> 00:01:28,360
Mother, what are you doing?
You know what this meeting is for.

24
00:01:28,490 --> 00:01:29,960
Please, calm down!

25
00:01:30,030 --> 00:01:33,030
Honey, what's wrong? Let's go home!
We can talk at home! All right?

26
00:01:35,130 --> 00:01:36,570
You listen to me, CEO Chae.

27
00:01:37,270 --> 00:01:42,140
I have proof you're having an affair
with my husband, Kang Nam Bong.

28
00:01:43,410 --> 00:01:45,810
So I've filed a lawsuit against you
for damages.

29
00:01:46,440 --> 00:01:51,380
After I get my money,
I'll use more evidence and sue you again.

30
00:01:51,720 --> 00:01:53,220
I'll sue you again and again...

31
00:01:53,720 --> 00:01:56,020
until this pain and humiliation
are washed away.

32
00:01:56,750 --> 00:01:59,420
- I will see this through to the very end.
- That's enough!

33
00:01:59,760 --> 00:02:04,560
We're here to plan our children's wedding.
How can you be so disrespectful here?

34
00:02:13,000 --> 00:02:14,010
Disrespectful?

35
00:02:14,770 --> 00:02:16,670
You're the one
who was disrespectful first!

36
00:02:17,380 --> 00:02:20,080
If future in-laws having an affair
isn't a disgrace, what is?

37
00:02:21,510 --> 00:02:23,920
The children's wedding can wait.

38
00:02:24,650 --> 00:02:28,490
First, we need to settle this affair
between you and my husband.

39
00:02:29,150 --> 00:02:31,020
Their wedding is not the priority here.

40
00:02:32,090 --> 00:02:34,390
What do you think you're doing?

41
00:02:34,490 --> 00:02:38,330
You're the one who started this
by wrecking my family!

42
00:02:39,100 --> 00:02:40,200
CEO Chae!

43
00:02:40,930 --> 00:02:43,470
Is this true?

44
00:02:45,600 --> 00:02:49,710
Oh my, her face is turning
all sorts of colors.

45
00:02:49,770 --> 00:02:53,080
I will never allow this marriage
to happen.

46
00:02:56,780 --> 00:02:59,750
I needed you to know the truth, Chairman.

47
00:03:00,750 --> 00:03:03,190
I know it was incredibly rude of me.

48
00:03:04,060 --> 00:03:05,390
I had to make a scene.

49
00:03:06,690 --> 00:03:07,690
Please forgive me.

50
00:03:12,360 --> 00:03:13,970
I'm so sorry.

51
00:03:17,370 --> 00:03:19,140
A fine mess you've made.

52
00:03:35,720 --> 00:03:38,260
(Suk Hee's Side Dishes)

53
00:03:40,560 --> 00:03:41,560
You're here?

54
00:03:44,400 --> 00:03:46,970
Everyone's at the Chairman's house, right?

55
00:03:49,930 --> 00:03:50,940
Baek Ho.

56
00:03:52,040 --> 00:03:53,070
Did you know about this?

57
00:03:53,370 --> 00:03:54,570
It's the formal family meeting today.

58
00:03:56,110 --> 00:03:59,580
My mom asked me to go,
but I said I was busy and bailed.

59
00:03:59,780 --> 00:04:01,780
You can't just be sitting around here.

60
00:04:02,050 --> 00:04:03,920
Go there, grab Jang Mi's hand,
and get her out of there.

61
00:04:04,220 --> 00:04:06,550
You have to expose everything
about Seo Rin. Cause a huge scene!

62
00:04:06,880 --> 00:04:08,590
- If you just let Jang Mi go like this...
- Enough.

63
00:04:09,390 --> 00:04:10,920
I'm just so upset for you, that's all.

64
00:04:12,560 --> 00:04:13,560
Don't worry.

65
00:04:14,130 --> 00:04:16,760
I'll find Ma Seo Rin before the wedding,
no matter what.

66
00:04:17,400 --> 00:04:19,560
And one way or another,
I'm going to stop this wedding.

67
00:04:19,660 --> 00:04:22,830
But we've called every nursing home,
even the ones in the countryside,

68
00:04:23,200 --> 00:04:26,940
and no one matched her description.
How are we ever going to find her?

69
00:04:27,340 --> 00:04:31,340
I found the driver of the ambulance
that took her.

70
00:04:31,540 --> 00:04:32,640
What?

71
00:04:32,940 --> 00:04:35,410
Then you know where she is?

72
00:04:35,410 --> 00:04:39,680
The driver doesn't remember exactly
where he dropped her off,

73
00:04:40,120 --> 00:04:44,160
- but he's sure it wasn't a hospital.
- If not a hospital, then where was it?

74
00:04:44,620 --> 00:04:46,360
He said it was a standalone house.

75
00:04:47,430 --> 00:04:48,930
I'm going to meet with that driver,

76
00:04:49,560 --> 00:04:51,800
and I swear I will find Ma Seo Rin.

77
00:04:56,500 --> 00:04:58,870
Father, that is absolutely not true.

78
00:04:59,370 --> 00:05:00,970
You must believe me.

79
00:05:01,610 --> 00:05:05,140
It's true I met with Professor Kang
a few times for a project,

80
00:05:05,410 --> 00:05:07,810
but absolutely nothing improper
happened between us.

81
00:05:08,450 --> 00:05:11,480
Lawyer Han must have misunderstood
what she saw.

82
00:05:12,180 --> 00:05:14,320
I married into the Dream family.

83
00:05:14,720 --> 00:05:19,660
I've never brought shame to Dong Seok
and have a clear conscience with Seo Rin.

84
00:05:19,760 --> 00:05:23,760
If that weren't true,
why would I ever let her marry Jun Ho?

85
00:05:23,760 --> 00:05:25,430
I'm telling the truth. Please believe me.

86
00:05:26,900 --> 00:05:27,900
Shut up!

87
00:05:29,030 --> 00:05:32,200
Until our Seo Rin becomes
the head of Dream Group,

88
00:05:32,270 --> 00:05:34,270
your only job
is to stay in the background.

89
00:05:34,410 --> 00:05:37,680
But you forgot your place
and caused a scandal like this?

90
00:05:38,140 --> 00:05:42,280
Did you think I wouldn't have known
about your affair?

91
00:05:42,750 --> 00:05:46,350
I figured as long as it wasn't exposed,
there'd be no problem.

92
00:05:46,550 --> 00:05:49,790
Father, I'm sorry.
I'll find a way to fix this.

93
00:05:50,350 --> 00:05:53,520
And I'll make sure Seo Rin's wedding
goes on as planned.

94
00:05:53,590 --> 00:05:56,290
That's not your call to make.

95
00:05:56,690 --> 00:05:59,800
Who are you to say
whether the wedding is on or off?

96
00:05:59,860 --> 00:06:03,370
Father, you have no idea
how much Seo Rin loves Jun Ho...

97
00:06:03,430 --> 00:06:04,440
Enough!

98
00:06:05,300 --> 00:06:06,300
Don't you know...

99
00:06:06,700 --> 00:06:09,610
what kind of trouble you're in right now?

100
00:06:09,870 --> 00:06:13,950
- How could you let things get this bad?
- Father.

101
00:06:13,950 --> 00:06:18,450
Don't you know our company lives and dies
by public perception?

102
00:06:18,720 --> 00:06:21,890
And yet, as the CEO,
you couldn't even factor that in...

103
00:06:21,950 --> 00:06:24,190
and acted on your own selfish impulses?

104
00:06:25,120 --> 00:06:27,990
I'm done wasting my breath.

105
00:06:28,760 --> 00:06:30,130
You've made this mess,

106
00:06:30,900 --> 00:06:32,300
so clean it up yourself.

107
00:06:49,210 --> 00:06:52,250
Getting caught by his wife and this is all
that happens? You should be thankful.

108
00:06:52,380 --> 00:06:53,920
Imagine she pulled your hair...

109
00:06:53,920 --> 00:06:55,850
and plastered your name
on the company bulletin board.

110
00:06:55,950 --> 00:06:57,760
- Think of the humiliation.
- Are you mocking me?

111
00:06:57,820 --> 00:06:58,820
Mocking you?

112
00:06:59,120 --> 00:07:01,890
- I'm just here to put your mind at ease.
- Shut up.

113
00:07:01,960 --> 00:07:05,330
Don't worry.
I'm going to marry Kang Jun Ho.

114
00:07:06,100 --> 00:07:07,870
Your goal is to take over
Dream Group, right?

115
00:07:09,230 --> 00:07:11,900
So you don't have to worry that
this scandal will ruin your plans.

116
00:07:13,140 --> 00:07:15,570
As if Chairman Ma is going
to be thrilled to let you get married now.

117
00:07:15,710 --> 00:07:17,910
An affair between the in-laws...

118
00:07:17,910 --> 00:07:19,240
I guess the blowback from that
would be huge.

119
00:07:20,040 --> 00:07:22,610
But I'll convince Grandpa.

120
00:07:23,180 --> 00:07:25,480
So just give me Seo Rin back.

121
00:07:26,350 --> 00:07:27,420
Where's Seo Rin?

122
00:07:27,620 --> 00:07:28,690
I knew it.

123
00:07:28,990 --> 00:07:31,560
- Blood is thicker than water, isn't it?
- It is.

124
00:07:31,560 --> 00:07:34,930
So, as long as you guarantee
that Seo Rin will be safe,

125
00:07:35,090 --> 00:07:37,460
I'll do whatever it takes,
even if it means marrying Kang Jun Ho.

126
00:07:37,930 --> 00:07:39,800
Give me my sister back right now.

127
00:07:40,060 --> 00:07:43,970
What if I just hand Seo Rin over to you,
and then you call off the wedding?

128
00:07:44,140 --> 00:07:47,710
Fine. Then I guess the wedding's off.

129
00:07:48,670 --> 00:07:49,670
Here's the deal.

130
00:07:50,410 --> 00:07:54,180
How about we trade
the wedding ceremony for Seo Rin?

131
00:08:02,290 --> 00:08:03,590
Who are you?

132
00:08:04,420 --> 00:08:05,860
Are you the one assigned to watch me?

133
00:08:06,660 --> 00:08:08,930
You look like some kind of
unlicensed caregiver,

134
00:08:09,460 --> 00:08:11,700
but you dare to take care of me
without any kind of license?

135
00:08:12,930 --> 00:08:14,200
What happened to Oh Jang Mi?

136
00:08:14,970 --> 00:08:15,970
And Grandpa...

137
00:08:16,470 --> 00:08:18,300
I wonder what happened to him.

138
00:08:29,680 --> 00:08:31,720
"Control through desire."

139
00:08:33,350 --> 00:08:36,290
You rule people by their own desires.

140
00:08:36,690 --> 00:08:40,930
So it means that the one
who controls and uses desire...

141
00:08:41,330 --> 00:08:43,330
holds all the power?

142
00:08:44,700 --> 00:08:46,660
- Exactly.
- Grandpa.

143
00:08:47,270 --> 00:08:49,270
Despite what happened today,

144
00:08:50,770 --> 00:08:53,370
I can't give up on Jun Ho.

145
00:08:54,270 --> 00:08:55,270
Please...

146
00:08:55,940 --> 00:08:57,410
let me marry him.

147
00:08:58,780 --> 00:09:01,350
Grandpa, please give us your blessing.

148
00:09:01,980 --> 00:09:02,980
I really...

149
00:09:04,450 --> 00:09:05,980
I really love Jun Ho.

150
00:09:06,620 --> 00:09:10,250
I'll marry Jun Ho
and help Dream Group prosper.

151
00:09:10,760 --> 00:09:13,560
I can do a better job
running it than my mother.

152
00:09:17,360 --> 00:09:22,230
Hey, Seo Rin is out of her mind.
She's trying to convince the Chairman.

153
00:09:22,300 --> 00:09:25,700
What? The Chairman will approve
the wedding after what just happened?

154
00:09:25,800 --> 00:09:29,270
That's what I'm talking about,
and Seo Rin said she must have Jun Ho.

155
00:09:29,410 --> 00:09:34,010
She claimed that with Jun Ho,
she can do what Hwa Young never could.

156
00:09:34,410 --> 00:09:35,410
Really?

157
00:09:36,010 --> 00:09:37,850
Still, I doubt it'll be easy
for them to get married.

158
00:09:38,250 --> 00:09:40,250
Didn't you see the look
on Lawyer Han's face?

159
00:09:40,320 --> 00:09:44,320
That family will be a wreck today.

160
00:09:45,660 --> 00:09:47,690
You're a terrifying woman.

161
00:09:48,090 --> 00:09:50,090
How could you cause a scene like that
in front of everyone?

162
00:09:50,360 --> 00:09:53,560
That was nothing
compared to what you did to me.

163
00:09:54,230 --> 00:09:57,340
Fine, whatever. Let's just get a divorce.
I'm begging you.

164
00:09:58,940 --> 00:10:00,300
Who said you can decide to divorce me?

165
00:10:01,010 --> 00:10:02,010
From now on,

166
00:10:02,410 --> 00:10:05,440
I will never give you anything you want.

167
00:10:05,880 --> 00:10:06,940
So don't even dream of it.

168
00:10:07,450 --> 00:10:09,680
You're going to pay the price
for underestimating me.

169
00:10:09,780 --> 00:10:12,320
I'm asking for a divorce!
Why are you being so stubborn?

170
00:10:14,620 --> 00:10:16,190
What do you two think you're doing?

171
00:10:18,260 --> 00:10:21,130
- Give up on marrying Director Ma.
- Give up?

172
00:10:21,730 --> 00:10:23,130
I will never do that.

173
00:10:23,290 --> 00:10:26,200
What? How can you say that
after the stunt your mother pulled today?

174
00:10:26,530 --> 00:10:28,270
Do you really think Chairman Ma
will give his blessing?

175
00:10:28,600 --> 00:10:31,770
You think he didn't know
about me and CEO Chae?

176
00:10:32,670 --> 00:10:36,610
He looked the other way
because it wasn't public knowledge.

177
00:10:37,910 --> 00:10:40,510
I'm so appalled that I can't even speak.

178
00:10:44,080 --> 00:10:45,080
So,

179
00:10:45,820 --> 00:10:47,620
are you telling me...

180
00:10:48,590 --> 00:10:51,420
that by exposing your filthy affair,

181
00:10:51,790 --> 00:10:55,160
I'm the one
who ruined our Jun Ho's marriage?

182
00:10:55,390 --> 00:10:58,100
Is that what you're trying to say?

183
00:10:58,100 --> 00:10:59,500
I'm just stating the facts.

184
00:10:59,660 --> 00:11:02,030
Would you have done this
if I were your biological son?

185
00:11:05,570 --> 00:11:06,570
Jun Ho!

186
00:11:07,870 --> 00:11:09,010
How can you say something like that?

187
00:11:09,070 --> 00:11:10,880
Search your hearts
and really think about it.

188
00:11:12,540 --> 00:11:14,150
If I had been your biological child,

189
00:11:15,280 --> 00:11:16,650
would you have acted
the way you did today?

190
00:11:22,620 --> 00:11:23,620
Jun Ho...

191
00:11:25,490 --> 00:11:26,990
How can you say something like that?

192
00:11:29,290 --> 00:11:31,200
No matter how important
your relationship is,

193
00:11:31,560 --> 00:11:32,560
at a time like this,

194
00:11:33,400 --> 00:11:34,870
you should be taking my side...

195
00:11:36,470 --> 00:11:38,500
and comforting me.
Shouldn't that come first?

196
00:11:39,670 --> 00:11:41,210
Are you that desperate to get married?

197
00:11:41,870 --> 00:11:46,210
Your mother is heartbroken and bleeding,

198
00:11:47,280 --> 00:11:48,710
and you are worried
about your marriage falling apart?

199
00:11:49,980 --> 00:11:51,350
Is that really your biggest concern
right now?

200
00:11:51,920 --> 00:11:52,920
That's enough.

201
00:11:53,320 --> 00:11:54,590
When you say things like that,

202
00:11:55,390 --> 00:11:56,950
do you think it doesn't hurt me?

203
00:11:57,820 --> 00:11:58,920
In a moment like this,

204
00:12:00,590 --> 00:12:02,060
do you really have to bring up...

205
00:12:02,660 --> 00:12:04,130
whether or not you're my real son?

206
00:12:06,530 --> 00:12:08,500
Even if you were my own flesh and blood...

207
00:12:09,030 --> 00:12:12,040
and my husband was cheating on me
with my son's future mother-in-law,

208
00:12:13,900 --> 00:12:15,510
I still would've retaliated the same way.

209
00:12:16,210 --> 00:12:20,210
I would've gone to Chairman Ma's house
and exposed it all the same. Why?

210
00:12:20,980 --> 00:12:24,080
- Was I so wrong for doing that?
- You didn't consider my feelings at all.

211
00:12:24,980 --> 00:12:27,950
If you drop a bomb like that
at the family meeting,

212
00:12:28,190 --> 00:12:30,450
it was obvious my wedding
would be called off, wasn't it?

213
00:12:30,720 --> 00:12:32,160
Kang Jun Ho, that's enough from you too.

214
00:12:34,590 --> 00:12:35,590
Whatever happens,

215
00:12:36,590 --> 00:12:37,760
let me make myself clear.

216
00:12:38,430 --> 00:12:40,030
No matter what happens,

217
00:12:41,130 --> 00:12:42,700
I am going to marry Ma Seo Rin.

218
00:12:43,270 --> 00:12:45,670
So, whether the two of you get divorced
or whatever else you do,

219
00:12:46,870 --> 00:12:47,940
I’m not going to stop you.

220
00:12:49,710 --> 00:12:50,710
But...

221
00:12:51,780 --> 00:12:53,080
do it after my wedding.

222
00:13:00,480 --> 00:13:01,490
That kid...

223
00:13:03,790 --> 00:13:07,090
See? You should've just held your tongue.
There are some things you just don't say.

224
00:13:08,060 --> 00:13:09,590
You're the one who messed up,

225
00:13:10,090 --> 00:13:11,130
so shut up.

226
00:13:14,570 --> 00:13:15,570
Who could that be?

227
00:13:17,170 --> 00:13:18,700
Hello, this is Kang Nam Bong.

228
00:13:21,370 --> 00:13:24,180
What? Secretary to Chairman Ma
of Dream Group?

229
00:13:24,580 --> 00:13:26,180
The Chairman would like you
to come to his home.

230
00:13:27,680 --> 00:13:28,680
Yes.

231
00:13:29,580 --> 00:13:30,580
So, is he coming?

232
00:13:30,650 --> 00:13:34,690
Yes, sir. But may I ask
why you've invited Professor Kang?

233
00:13:34,890 --> 00:13:35,920
Are you curious?

234
00:13:36,750 --> 00:13:37,790
You must be wondering...

235
00:13:38,290 --> 00:13:41,890
why I approved the marriage
between Professor Kang's son and Seo Rin.

236
00:13:42,430 --> 00:13:43,430
Yes, sir.

237
00:13:44,060 --> 00:13:45,300
At first,

238
00:13:45,800 --> 00:13:47,770
I thought that CEO Chae
and Professor Kang...

239
00:13:48,200 --> 00:13:50,030
were in it together.

240
00:13:51,940 --> 00:13:54,240
After CEO Chae
accidentally killed someone,

241
00:13:54,970 --> 00:13:59,610
I figured Professor Kang
took the fall for her out of love.

242
00:14:00,410 --> 00:14:02,750
But I was wrong.

243
00:14:03,650 --> 00:14:04,650
You were wrong?

244
00:14:04,950 --> 00:14:06,780
CEO Chae framed him.

245
00:14:07,520 --> 00:14:08,690
And that's the problem.

246
00:14:10,350 --> 00:14:15,060
Professor Kang had no idea.
He was completely duped by CEO Chae.

247
00:14:15,430 --> 00:14:16,690
She just used him.

248
00:14:17,190 --> 00:14:18,500
And she's still using him.

249
00:14:19,200 --> 00:14:22,130
He probably has his suspicions.

250
00:14:23,730 --> 00:14:25,000
But here's the thing.

251
00:14:25,670 --> 00:14:27,200
If Professor Kang...

252
00:14:28,670 --> 00:14:30,980
were to find out the whole truth...

253
00:14:31,540 --> 00:14:33,210
I'm not worried about Professor Kang.

254
00:14:33,240 --> 00:14:36,310
I'm worried about his wife, Lawyer Han.

255
00:14:37,620 --> 00:14:40,680
If she finds out her husband is being used
and decides to act on it,

256
00:14:40,990 --> 00:14:43,050
it would be a disaster for our company.

257
00:14:43,290 --> 00:14:46,160
She'll try to clear his name.
After all, he's the father of her kids.

258
00:14:46,160 --> 00:14:47,190
That's right.

259
00:14:48,790 --> 00:14:50,430
If it's revealed
that my daughter-in-law...

260
00:14:50,490 --> 00:14:54,130
covered up a murder a murder
and aided in it,

261
00:14:54,470 --> 00:14:57,330
the blow to our company
would be catastrophic.

262
00:14:57,870 --> 00:14:59,440
And my Seo Rin...

263
00:15:01,040 --> 00:15:05,140
Her image as the successor
would be completely destroyed.

264
00:15:05,410 --> 00:15:07,780
But can a marriage really
cover all that up?

265
00:15:09,580 --> 00:15:12,050
Marriage is a union between two families.

266
00:15:13,280 --> 00:15:15,090
If we bind them to us as in-laws,

267
00:15:16,050 --> 00:15:17,790
they won't dare make a move against us.

268
00:15:19,990 --> 00:15:23,760
Making them family
so they can't be our enemies.

269
00:15:24,530 --> 00:15:26,260
Since that was the best option for now,

270
00:15:27,130 --> 00:15:30,470
I planned to have
Jun Ho and Seo Rin get married.

271
00:15:31,270 --> 00:15:33,840
You've thought of everything, Chairman.

272
00:15:34,200 --> 00:15:36,740
And it would also do wonders
for the company's public image.

273
00:15:38,040 --> 00:15:40,840
It's not another strategic marriage
between two families.

274
00:15:42,080 --> 00:15:43,810
It's my granddaughter’s marriage
to an ordinary employee,

275
00:15:43,810 --> 00:15:45,450
based on nothing but love.

276
00:15:45,850 --> 00:15:49,250
That's the kind of fairytale
people dream about.

277
00:15:49,450 --> 00:15:53,790
Kang Jun Ho is the perfect candidate
for that narrative,

278
00:15:54,530 --> 00:15:57,130
Our stock price will go up, naturally.

279
00:16:00,630 --> 00:16:03,500
Jun Ho, don't you care about Mom at all?

280
00:16:04,340 --> 00:16:06,440
Do you really have to break her heart
like this?

281
00:16:06,500 --> 00:16:08,340
Don't act like you're the only one
who cares about Mom.

282
00:16:09,410 --> 00:16:11,580
You're secretly relieved about all this,
aren't you?

283
00:16:12,010 --> 00:16:13,280
What are you talking about?

284
00:16:13,340 --> 00:16:16,780
You're happy I can't marry Oh Jang Mi
because of Dad, aren't you?

285
00:16:16,850 --> 00:16:18,780
Trying to force the wedding
in this situation...

286
00:16:19,250 --> 00:16:20,520
is just unreasonable.

287
00:16:20,980 --> 00:16:24,020
- Can't you at least give Mom some time?
- Just be honest with me.

288
00:16:24,920 --> 00:16:26,390
Stop using Mom as an excuse.

289
00:16:27,290 --> 00:16:29,190
You don't want me to marry Jang Mi,

290
00:16:29,490 --> 00:16:32,660
- Admit it.
- Fine. If she marries you,

291
00:16:32,930 --> 00:16:35,370
I know she'll be miserable,
and it breaks my heart.

292
00:16:35,630 --> 00:16:37,570
- That's why I have to stop you.
- Shut up.

293
00:16:38,400 --> 00:16:40,540
I'm rushing this wedding...

294
00:16:41,270 --> 00:16:42,510
because of you.

295
00:16:43,310 --> 00:16:44,710
So don't even get any ideas.

296
00:16:45,180 --> 00:16:46,840
I'm going to marry Jang Mi,
and that's final.

297
00:17:04,930 --> 00:17:06,330
Grandpa wants to see you in his study.

298
00:17:07,230 --> 00:17:09,200
- Why?
- How should I know?

299
00:17:16,110 --> 00:17:17,110
Father.

300
00:17:22,180 --> 00:17:23,550
Come in. Stand there.

301
00:17:28,290 --> 00:17:29,350
Well...

302
00:17:30,350 --> 00:17:35,330
- What is this about?
- You know exactly what this is about.

303
00:17:35,560 --> 00:17:39,130
Chairman, I'm so sorry
for causing you all this trouble.

304
00:17:39,260 --> 00:17:41,730
Then why do things
you'll have to apologize for?

305
00:17:43,330 --> 00:17:45,100
Tell me, to my face.

306
00:17:45,840 --> 00:17:48,440
Are the two of you in love?

307
00:17:48,670 --> 00:17:49,940
- Yes, we are.
- No, we're not.

308
00:17:51,140 --> 00:17:52,140
Nam Bong.

309
00:17:53,210 --> 00:17:57,210
That's not true, Father.
He's been pursuing me this whole time.

310
00:17:58,120 --> 00:18:00,150
It's hard enough being a widow,

311
00:18:00,550 --> 00:18:04,620
but he saw me as a target and stalked me.
That's why we're in this mess, Father.

312
00:18:05,360 --> 00:18:07,930
Hwa Young, how can you say such a thing?

313
00:18:08,230 --> 00:18:11,900
- Me, a stalker? That's ridiculous.
- You darn stalker!

314
00:18:12,730 --> 00:18:17,170
Are you going to keep harassing
my daughter-in-law or not?

315
00:18:18,070 --> 00:18:21,470
What are you doing at nearly 60 years old?

316
00:18:21,710 --> 00:18:24,040
- Father.
- Get out of my way!

317
00:18:24,370 --> 00:18:28,150
You said he's a stalker.
He deserves to be treated like one.

318
00:18:28,380 --> 00:18:31,010
- But you can't treat a person this way...
- A person?

319
00:18:31,420 --> 00:18:33,350
The fact that you still see him
as a person...

320
00:18:33,420 --> 00:18:36,050
means what Professor Kang said
wasn't entirely a lie after all.

321
00:18:36,120 --> 00:18:37,120
No.

322
00:18:37,750 --> 00:18:40,420
- That's not what I meant...
- Yes, it's true.

323
00:18:40,990 --> 00:18:42,890
I stalked her.

324
00:18:43,230 --> 00:18:46,200
I'll never love Hwa Young again.

325
00:18:46,960 --> 00:18:48,900
You should've just said that
from the start.

326
00:18:50,530 --> 00:18:54,810
Marriage isn't just about two people.
It's about two families.

327
00:18:55,240 --> 00:18:58,110
If the parents are mired in scandal,

328
00:18:58,440 --> 00:19:01,310
how can their children possibly be happy?

329
00:19:01,750 --> 00:19:05,350
The least you could do as parents is
wish for your children's happiness.

330
00:19:06,950 --> 00:19:09,890
- I was wrong, Chairman.
- So for the kids' wedding,

331
00:19:10,490 --> 00:19:11,990
are you giving your permission?

332
00:19:12,060 --> 00:19:15,730
Seo Rin and Jun Ho say they're in love.

333
00:19:16,230 --> 00:19:18,530
They're the ones in love, not you.

334
00:19:20,130 --> 00:19:21,300
Now, listen to me.

335
00:19:21,300 --> 00:19:23,170
After today,

336
00:19:23,300 --> 00:19:26,070
if I hear a peep about the two of you
being in love,

337
00:19:27,040 --> 00:19:29,870
I promise you it won't end like this.

338
00:19:30,410 --> 00:19:31,580
Mark my words!

339
00:19:32,510 --> 00:19:33,510
Yes, sir.

340
00:19:36,310 --> 00:19:38,520
(Bomdama)

341
00:19:40,050 --> 00:19:42,890
What? Seo Rin's at a private home?

342
00:19:43,050 --> 00:19:45,990
Baek Ho said the ambulance driver
didn't take her to a hospital.

343
00:19:46,060 --> 00:19:47,760
The driver dropped her off
at a private home.

344
00:19:47,760 --> 00:19:49,790
Then we should be able to find her soon!

345
00:19:50,130 --> 00:19:52,260
And if that happens,
Jang Mi won't have to marry Jun Ho,

346
00:19:52,330 --> 00:19:55,100
- and she could be with Baek Ho, right?
- Exactly.

347
00:19:55,630 --> 00:19:58,300
But Seo Rin is Chae Hwa Young's captive
right now,

348
00:19:58,640 --> 00:20:01,340
and we're terrified she might hurt her.

349
00:20:01,670 --> 00:20:03,810
That's why we're just going along
with her demands for now.

350
00:20:04,980 --> 00:20:07,880
That woman is the devil incarnate.

351
00:20:08,480 --> 00:20:13,280
Anyway, as twins, Seo Rin and Jang Mi
must look identical, right?

352
00:20:14,620 --> 00:20:16,820
- I can't wait to meet her.
- Me too.

353
00:20:18,160 --> 00:20:19,760
The shop is so bright and clean.

354
00:20:20,120 --> 00:20:21,830
I bet Seo Rin will love it
when she gets here.

355
00:20:23,490 --> 00:20:26,900
But Mom keeps complaining about headaches.
It's a little strange.

356
00:20:28,270 --> 00:20:29,830
Her memories might be coming back?

357
00:20:34,710 --> 00:20:36,270
No... My babies...

358
00:20:50,350 --> 00:20:51,360
No!

359
00:20:55,690 --> 00:20:56,990
Where am I?

360
00:20:58,630 --> 00:20:59,760
My baby...

361
00:21:00,160 --> 00:21:02,300
Grandma, were you having a nightmare?

362
00:21:03,130 --> 00:21:05,240
Grandma, are you looking
for Ok Hee and Tok Hee?

363
00:21:05,940 --> 00:21:08,040
You always look for Ok Hee and Tok Hee.

364
00:21:09,210 --> 00:21:10,240
What was that?

365
00:21:25,890 --> 00:21:28,030
Tok Hee is right here.

366
00:21:30,390 --> 00:21:32,030
Jang Mi is so pretty.

367
00:21:32,460 --> 00:21:33,900
But Grandma...

368
00:21:34,400 --> 00:21:38,840
- What?
- Are you okay? You seem a little strange.

369
00:21:44,010 --> 00:21:46,240
I miss Jang Mi.

370
00:21:53,980 --> 00:21:55,020
Yes, CEO.

371
00:21:55,990 --> 00:21:56,990
Mom?

372
00:21:59,390 --> 00:22:02,890
Her breathing is normal,
but she's still not showing any movement.

373
00:22:07,500 --> 00:22:09,200
Why did she leave me in a place like this?

374
00:22:09,770 --> 00:22:11,200
This isn't even a hospital.

375
00:22:11,900 --> 00:22:14,300
Where on earth am I?

376
00:22:39,630 --> 00:22:40,700
Mother.

377
00:22:41,800 --> 00:22:45,400
- Seo Rin is here.
- May I come in?

378
00:22:48,510 --> 00:22:49,510
Jun Ho.

379
00:22:50,110 --> 00:22:51,110
Could you bring me some cutlery?

380
00:22:51,740 --> 00:22:52,780
Okay.

381
00:23:03,450 --> 00:23:04,490
Director Ma.

382
00:23:05,560 --> 00:23:07,020
What brings you here so suddenly?

383
00:23:07,490 --> 00:23:09,360
I know you must be heartbroken,

384
00:23:09,990 --> 00:23:12,330
and I'm sorry for showing up unannounced.

385
00:23:12,830 --> 00:23:15,100
I have a headache. Just leave.

386
00:23:16,730 --> 00:23:18,030
Your mother is having an affair...

387
00:23:19,300 --> 00:23:23,210
with my husband.
I'm sure you're aware of that.

388
00:23:23,370 --> 00:23:24,780
I can only imagine how difficult...

389
00:23:25,740 --> 00:23:27,240
and painful this must be for you.

390
00:23:30,950 --> 00:23:32,020
Why would you say that?

391
00:23:34,080 --> 00:23:38,190
It must feel like your entire life
has been a lie.

392
00:23:40,860 --> 00:23:42,160
Seo Rin,

393
00:23:42,990 --> 00:23:44,660
I'm not looking for your sympathy,

394
00:23:45,500 --> 00:23:46,500
so just go.

395
00:23:48,800 --> 00:23:52,100
I didn't come to ask for your approval
for our marriage.

396
00:23:52,940 --> 00:23:56,370
I came because I was worried
you might make yourself sick over this.

397
00:23:57,770 --> 00:23:58,780
I brought you this...

398
00:24:12,420 --> 00:24:14,290
I wasn't sure what you'd like,

399
00:24:14,760 --> 00:24:17,060
so I asked Jun Ho,

400
00:24:17,060 --> 00:24:18,730
and he told me
you enjoy sweet pumpkin porridge.

401
00:24:19,000 --> 00:24:22,300
I made it for you myself.
But I'm not sure if it's to your liking.

402
00:24:22,600 --> 00:24:23,700
You...

403
00:24:24,670 --> 00:24:26,740
know how to make things like this?

404
00:24:28,470 --> 00:24:29,640
You grew up so sheltered,

405
00:24:30,710 --> 00:24:32,910
I thought you didn't know the first thing
about being in a kitchen.

406
00:24:33,410 --> 00:24:35,410
I actually enjoy cooking
from time to time.

407
00:24:36,410 --> 00:24:38,320
I'm not sure if it's to your taste,

408
00:24:38,750 --> 00:24:41,220
But try some, please.

409
00:24:41,220 --> 00:24:42,550
This is all so sudden...

410
00:24:45,660 --> 00:24:47,460
Since you went to all this trouble,

411
00:24:48,190 --> 00:24:49,560
I can't very well refuse.

412
00:24:59,740 --> 00:25:00,740
How is it?

413
00:25:04,880 --> 00:25:07,440
I was hoping it would help you
get your strength back.

414
00:25:14,050 --> 00:25:15,450
It smells amazing.

415
00:25:16,420 --> 00:25:17,950
I think I taste some heavy cream,

416
00:25:18,890 --> 00:25:22,360
- and a hint of pine nuts, too.
- Spoken like a true chef.

417
00:25:22,830 --> 00:25:24,630
Porridge is easy to eat,

418
00:25:25,400 --> 00:25:27,530
and I thought it would be good
for regaining your strength.

419
00:25:36,870 --> 00:25:40,580
I'm thinking of having you...

420
00:25:40,580 --> 00:25:42,980
draft Seo Rin's marriage contract.

421
00:25:44,510 --> 00:25:46,280
I know how to keep business
and personal matters separate.

422
00:25:50,390 --> 00:25:54,190
I knew my judgment of character
wasn't wrong.

423
00:25:55,030 --> 00:25:57,130
Under civil law, marriage is an act
that affects personal status.

424
00:25:57,390 --> 00:25:59,660
So even if you include provisions
to limit inheritance,

425
00:26:00,000 --> 00:26:02,830
the contract won't be legally binding
under domestic law.

426
00:26:03,630 --> 00:26:07,200
But if CEO Chae sees the contract,

427
00:26:08,440 --> 00:26:10,570
she'll feel threatened, won't she?

428
00:26:11,780 --> 00:26:15,650
That's why you're in a hurry
to revise your will.

429
00:26:31,630 --> 00:26:32,630
What do you think you're doing?

430
00:26:33,460 --> 00:26:34,500
Get out of my chair.

431
00:26:34,560 --> 00:26:38,470
This chair will be mine anyway
once I marry Jun Ho.

432
00:26:38,770 --> 00:26:40,570
So I thought I'd try it out.

433
00:26:40,640 --> 00:26:41,770
(CEO Chae Hwa Young)

434
00:26:41,840 --> 00:26:43,910
Look at you, so full of yourself.

435
00:26:44,170 --> 00:26:46,910
Fine. Did you win over Lawyer Han?

436
00:26:47,010 --> 00:26:50,150
Yes. She gave me her blessing
to get married.

437
00:26:50,910 --> 00:26:51,920
No way!

438
00:26:52,420 --> 00:26:54,620
How on earth did you wrap her
around your finger?

439
00:26:54,750 --> 00:26:58,720
- That's none of your business.
- You're a pro at manipulating people.

440
00:26:59,060 --> 00:27:02,230
I guess that's how you got your hooks
into my Jun Ho.

441
00:27:02,290 --> 00:27:04,590
I guess you think
everyone is just like you.

442
00:27:04,760 --> 00:27:06,830
Go ahead and believe whatever you want.

443
00:27:12,840 --> 00:27:15,610
(Marriage Contract)

444
00:27:30,420 --> 00:27:31,960
I have to save Seo Rin first.

445
00:27:33,820 --> 00:27:35,090
I'm so sorry, Baek Ho.

446
00:27:46,740 --> 00:27:49,770
That vixen, Oh Jang Mi,
managed to convince Chairman Ma.

447
00:27:50,010 --> 00:27:52,780
Are you planning to accept her terms?

448
00:27:52,780 --> 00:27:54,540
You still don't know me at all, do you?

449
00:27:54,710 --> 00:27:57,610
Do you really think I'd give in to demands
from Oh Jang Mi?

450
00:27:58,580 --> 00:28:00,080
Why would I ever hand over Seo Rin?

451
00:28:00,750 --> 00:28:02,720
She could be a ticking time bomb for me.

452
00:28:03,090 --> 00:28:04,090
Then...

453
00:28:04,620 --> 00:28:08,430
Oh Jang Mi is acting like
she has nine lives.

454
00:28:08,890 --> 00:28:12,400
Once Seo Rin wakes up,
get rid of Oh Jang Mi.

455
00:28:12,630 --> 00:28:17,330
- Understood.
- In any case, we don't need the twins.

456
00:28:17,770 --> 00:28:18,770
Absolutely not.

457
00:28:19,200 --> 00:28:21,570
That's how it was back then,
and that's how it is now.

458
00:28:22,840 --> 00:28:25,180
One of them has to die.

459
00:28:26,440 --> 00:28:28,310
One of us has to die?

460
00:28:29,050 --> 00:28:33,320
Does that mean she tried
to kill Oh Jang Mi with that truck?

461
00:29:07,150 --> 00:29:08,790
(The First Man)

462
00:29:08,950 --> 00:29:10,290
I'm here looking for someone.

463
00:29:10,450 --> 00:29:13,390
- Hey, stop right there! Get him!
- Ma Seo Rin!

464
00:29:13,490 --> 00:29:15,990
All this time, Oh Jang Mi
has been pretending to be me.

465
00:29:16,790 --> 00:29:18,260
How dare you pretend to be me?

466
00:29:18,660 --> 00:29:21,700
- Ma Seo Rin, snap out of it!
- Shut up, Oh Jang Mi!

467
00:29:22,200 --> 00:29:26,600
You're the one who tried to make me
marry your son, Kang Jun Ho.

468
00:29:26,600 --> 00:29:29,910
- Oh Jang Mi!
- Is Jun Ho your son, Mom?

469
00:29:31,880 --> 00:29:33,880
(Subtitles are provided by KOCOWA.)
